        a. Problem Solving...
       ﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄ

           The only/biggest  problem I  have had  people have when
           using  NetModem/NetFOSSIL is people dont load NetFOSSIL
           in thier AUTOEXEC.BAT, instead  they  load it in  thier
           DOS Window. It will not  work  that  way,  it  must  be
           loaded in the AUTOEXEC.BAT.

           Another problem is that sometimes they forget that they
           are loading another FOSSIL Driver on the same  port  as
           NetFOSSIL. This can cause problems so make  sure if you
           are loading another FOSSIL Driver that you dont use the
           same COM port as NetFOSSIL is going to support/emulate.

           Another problem is that people think  you have to  tell
           NetFOSSIL the COM port your real modem is on. No you do
           not do this, you tell NetFOSSIL a COM port to "Emulate"

           Other problems have been due to NetFOSSIL  bugs, & have
           been fixed. If you encounter any problems and have done
           everything right, then contact me via EMail and give me
           a  detailed  message describing  your problem, and what
           BBS software you are using...

