        c. Future Versions...
       ﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄﾄ

           Most of these features are planned for  NetModem/32 and
           will  probably  only  be  features  of  the  Registered
           version but possible for NetModem.

           - Better GUI.
           - Caller ID.
           - IP/Domain Blocking to block out certain IP's or
             Domains.
           - More control over the Server.
           - Statistics Display.
           - Editable Text files to display when a certain event
             has occured like "BBS is not ready" or "Connecting,
             please wait...".
           - Definable Timeout to determine if the BBS is not
             answering.
           - Connection Log(s).
           - User Definable Buffer sizes in the FOSSIL driver.
           - True 32bit/Multi-Threaded code. (NetModem/32)
           - Support for WinSock 2.0 (32bit anyway) and 32bit
             WinSock 1.1.
           - NT Support - If I can somehow create an NT based
             FOSSIL driver. If anyone has any info EMail me.
             (drip@cris.com)
           - Any other ideas users have or that I may come up with.
           
